'''Ōarahiko Shrine''' (おおあらひこじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Yasuigawa, Shin-Asahi-chō, {{ill|lt=Takashima|Q845794|WD=Q845794|1=Takashima, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. Until early {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}}, it was called '''Kawachi Daimyōjin'''. It is a {{ill|lt=candidate shrine|Q135022904|WD=Q135022904|1=Shikinai Ronsha}} for a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}. The {{ill|lt=annual festival|Q11385469|WD=Q11385469|1=Reisai}} is the '''Nanakawa Festival'''. Its former shrine rank was {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōaratawake-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}
* {{ill|lt=Toyoki-iri-hiko-no-Mikoto|Q11633375|WD=Q11633375|1=Prince Toyokiirihiko}}
These two are the main deities; additionally enshrined are {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Sukunahikona-no-Mikoto|1=Sukunabikona|WD=Q3275687}}, {{ill|lt=Emperor Nintoku|Q313119|WD=Q313119|1=Emperor Nintoku}}, {{ill|lt=Emperor Uda|Q349267|WD=Q349267|1=Emperor Uda}}, and {{ill|lt=Imperial Prince Atsumi|Q11499521|WD=Q11499521|1=Atsumi-shinnō}}. The main deities are said to grant victory.

=== Shrine crest ===
Hira-yottsume

=== Origin ===
{{節スタブ}}

=== Rituals ===
=== Sacred events ===
* Nanakawa Festival
:Held on May 4. Includes "yakko-furi" and {{ill|lt=yabusame|Q1886157|WD=Q1886157|1=Yabusame}}, and is said to be the leading festival in the Kosei area of Shiga. "Yakko-furi" (target procession, barrel-swinging) is selected as a Shiga Prefecture intangible folk cultural property. The barrel-swinging “witticisms” are bawdy and entertain spectators.
* Kentō Festival
:A summer festival organized by the Ōarahiko Shrine parish youth association, held in mid-August.

=== Shrine families ===
:According to the Kitano Tenmangū document ''Meian-tō Shoki Roku Kakinuki'' (record of December 4, {{ill|lt=Bun'an|Q1193586|WD=Q1193586|1=Bun'an}} 4), the shrine family at that time was involved in conflict between {{ill|lt=Enryaku-ji|Q917195|WD=Q917195|1=Enryaku-ji}} and the {{ill|lt=Takashima clan|Q11669657|WD=Q11669657|1=Takashima clan}}, and was exiled to {{ill|lt=Kyushu|Q13987|WD=Q13987|1=Kyushu}}. Thereafter, worship has continued through the current shrine family.

